<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="525" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Prof. Eudóxia M. Froehlich kept in her office the histological slides of most land planarians studied by Marcus. Histological slides in her collection include more than 
<specimenCount box="[939,1097,188,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
labeled only “hina”. Marcus presented diagrammatic reconstructions of the pharynx and the copulatory apparatus of the 
<typeStatus box="[1167,1265,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">holotype</typeStatus>
(Figs. 
<quantity metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6421" metricValueMax="6.7056" metricValueMin="6.5786" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" unit="in" value="261.5" valueMax="264.0" valueMin="259.0">259-264 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus, E." box="[188,355,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" pagination="5 - 215" refId="ref14818" refString="Marcus, E. (1951) Turbellaria brasileiros (9). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Serie Zoologia, 16, 5 - 215." type="journal article" year="1951">Marcus, 1951</bibRefCitation>
). These reconstructions fully match the organs on the histological sections of what we consequently consider to be the 
<typeStatus box="[511,613,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus, E." box="[199,367,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" pagination="5 - 215" refId="ref14818" refString="Marcus, E. (1951) Turbellaria brasileiros (9). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Serie Zoologia, 16, 5 - 215." type="journal article" year="1951">Marcus (1951)</bibRefCitation>
described the distal portion of the penis papilla as housed in a ventral pouch of the female atrium. Our interpretation of parasagittal sections of the 
<specimenCount box="[786,953,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
is that the presumed pouch is actually part of the single space constituting the female atrium which is partially occluded by its own lateral fold. Marcus also distinguished a short female genital duct -which is lined with ciliated epithelium-, from a dorsal diverticulum of the female atrium -lined with a nonciliated epithelium, after Marcus. However, we were unable to make this distinction since both epithelia are non ciliated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">
<bibRefCitation author="Carbayo, F. &amp; Alvarez-Presas, M. &amp; Olivares, M. T. &amp; Marques, F. P. L. &amp; Froehlich, E. M. &amp; Riutort, M." box="[199,437,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" pagination="508 - 528" refId="ref14412" refString="Carbayo, F., Alvarez-Presas, M., Olivares, M. T., Marques, F. P. L., Froehlich, E. M. &amp; Riutort, M. (2013) Molecular phylogeny of Geoplaninae (Platyhelminthes) challenges current classification: proposal of taxonomic actions. Zoologica Scripta, 42, 508 - 528. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / zsc. 12019" type="journal article" year="2013">
Carbayo 
<emphasis box="[300,356,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
included the specimen MZUSP PL 
<quantity box="[840,925,548,573]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.56032" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" unit="in" value="1008.0">1008 in</quantity>
their molecular analyses. They identified this specimen as 
<taxonomicName authority="Marcus, 1951" authorityName="Marcus" authorityYear="1951" box="[293,623,583,608]" family="Geoplanidae" genus="Geoplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="hina">
<emphasis box="[293,460,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">Geoplana hina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus, E." box="[467,623,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" pagination="5 - 215" refId="ref14818" refString="Marcus, E. (1951) Turbellaria brasileiros (9). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Serie Zoologia, 16, 5 - 215." type="journal article" year="1951">Marcus, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Although very alike, the external aspect and the copulatory apparatus of this specimen do not fully match diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marcus" authorityYear="1951" box="[667,750,620,645]" family="Geoplanidae" genus="Geoplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="hina">
<emphasis box="[667,750,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">C. hina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See below the section Remarks on 
<taxonomicName authority="Lago-Barcia &amp; Carbayo, 2018" authorityName="Lago-Barcia &amp; Carbayo" authorityYear="2018" box="[1156,1321,620,644]" family="Geoplanidae" genus="Cratera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="picuia" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1156,1321,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">Cratera picuia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1328,1391,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1328,1391,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
